name: Baku Zoological Park
description: {'Information:': ['Baku Zoological Park is one of the oldest and largest zoos in Azerbaijan. Located in the heart of Baku, it houses a diverse range of local and international animals. The park was established in 1928 and has since become a popular tourist destination for both residents and visitors.'], 'Main Features:': ['It includes more than 100 types of animals from all over the world.', 'It contains educational areas for children on animal protection and the environment.', 'The garden is equipped with places to sit and rest in the green spaces.', 'It contains small lakes and places for cycling and walking.', 'They include wild animal areas, reptiles, tin, and mammals.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['It is preferable to visit the park in the morning to enjoy its quiet atmosphere before visitors crowd.', 'Make sure to wear comfortable clothes, as the garden is wide and visitors need to walk for long periods.', 'Remember taking the camera to take pictures of animals and landscapes.', 'If you are with children, they can enjoy the garden game area.']}

name: National Seaside Park
description: {'Information:': ['The National Maritime Park is located in Baku along the beaches of the Caspian Sea and is considered one of the largest and most beautiful green spaces in the capital, and it is an ideal place to relax and hike with great views of the sea.'], 'Main Features:': ['It extends over a great distance near the beach, making it a famous destination for tourists and locals.', 'It contains wide walking paths and gardens, providing a suitable place for family picnics.', 'Many fountains, statues, and entertainment places include children.', 'It provides great views of the Caspian Sea and the Paku Horizon.', 'An ideal place for light sports or enjoying walking on the beach.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['It is preferable to visit it in the evening to enjoy the beautiful sunset scenes.', 'It is good to wear comfortable shoes to walk in long tracks.', 'If you like photography, the place is perfect for taking great pictures.', 'Make sure to relax near the sea to enjoy the calm atmosphere.']}

name: Heydar Mosque
description: {'Information:': ['The Heydar Mosque is the largest mosque in Baku and Azerbaijan and was opened in 2014 and was named after the national leader Haider Aliyev and is characterized by a luxurious architectural design that mixes the traditional and modern Islamic style.'], 'Main Features:': ['It is considered one of the largest mosques in the Caucasus area with a capacity of 75,000 worshipers.', 'Its architectural design is dazzled by its four domes and tall minarets of up to 95 meters.', 'Decorated with precise stone works and beautiful Islamic decorations inside and outside.', 'Equipped with the latest sound and lighting technologies.', 'A wide square surrounding the mosque gives a feeling of prestige and tranquility.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['It is preferable to visit it at sunset to enjoy the beauty of external lighting.', 'Make sure to wear modest clothes to respect the religious place.', 'Tourists are allowed to enter outside prayer times.', 'Do not forget to take pictures, but calmly and without disturbing the worshipers.']}
short_description: The largest mosque in Azerbaijan, characterized by its wonderful design and large capacity of 75,000 worshipers.

name: Huseyn Javid Park
description: {'Information:': ['Hussein Park is located in the heart of Baku, Azerbaijan and was called in honor of the famous Azerbaijani poet and playwright Hussein Javed and the garden is a quiet and perfect place to relax in nature.'], 'Main Features:': ['It includes a memorial statue of Hussein Javed, which reflects the importance of Azerbaijani literature and culture.', 'Wide green spaces and shadow trees are perfect for picnics and walking.', 'Sitting seats and places designated for children to play.', 'Close to other cultural features in Baku.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['The most appropriate time to visit is during the day to enjoy the beauty of nature and calm.', 'The place is suitable for reading or relaxing away from the bustle of the city.', "Don't forget to take a picture next to the statue of Hussein Javed!", 'Wear a comfortable shoe if you intend to roam inside the garden.']}
short_description: A quiet garden in Baku, which includes the statue of Hussein Javed, ideal for relaxing in nature.

name: Philharmonic Fountain
description: {'Information:': ['Philharmonic fountain is located in the Philharmouni Park next to the Philharmouni National Hall in Baku, Azerbaijan and is considered one of the most famous places to relax and enjoy calm in the old city in the old city.'], 'Main Features:': ['A beautiful classic design belonging to the Soviet era.', 'Surrounded by Flower Flower Veldharmoni gardens.', 'It is close to historical monuments such as the Shiruanchehan Palace and Nizami Street.', 'Perfect place for hiking or relaxing next to the fountain.', 'Sometimes a musical atmosphere because of its proximity to the concert hall.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['Visit it early in the morning or sunset to enjoy the calm atmosphere.', 'A great opportunity to take memorial photos with an elegant architectural background.', 'You can combine her visit and visit the Philharmonic Hall, or hike in the old city.', "Don't forget to enjoy a coffee session in a nearby café!"]}

name: Absheron National Park
description: {'Information:': ['Abshiron National Park is located in the Absheron Peninsula, southeast of Baku, Azerbaijan and was founded in 2005 with the aim of protecting the unique biological diversity in the region and is home to many rare and endangered species.'], 'Main Features:': ['It extends over an area of \u200b\u200b783 hectares of natural lands.', 'A home to wild animals such as deer, foxes, wild rabbits, Caspian Sea, rare birds such as seagulls and eagles.', 'Environmental diversity between sandy plains, dunes, and salty bodies.', 'Wonderful views of the Caspian Sea with an opportunity to see wildlife in its natural environment.', 'Ideal for nature lovers and walking for long distances.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['It is preferable to wear comfortable shoes and clothes suitable for hot and dry weather.', 'Bring with you drinking water and snacks, as there are no stores inside the park.', 'The best time to visit is in the morning or end of the day to avoid the heat of the afternoon.', 'Adhere to the specified paths to maintain the ecosystem and not disturb animals.', 'Do not forget the camera to take pictures of nature and a unique wildlife!']}
short_description: The Abshiron National Park is a natural haven that includes a rare wildlife and stunning views of the Caspian Sea.

name: Shahidlar Monument
description: {'Information:': ['Shahidlar Monument is located in Baku, Azerbaijan, within the Highland Park, overlooking the Caspian Sea and the city horizon line.'], 'The importance:': ['The memory of the Martyrs of January (1990) and the war victims between Azerbaijan and Armenia commemorates.', 'It is one of the most important national monuments that honor those who sacrificed their lives for the independence of Azerbaijan.', 'It is symbolized as a place to meditate and respect by visitors and citizens alike.'], 'Main Features:': ['It includes an eternal flame that remains burning in honor of the martyrs.', 'A quiet area overlooking panoramic views of the city and the sea.', 'The monument is surrounded by corridors and green gardens that provide a comfortable atmosphere for meditation.', 'It is located near the Highland Park and Baku Eye, making it a main station on the city tour.'], 'Tips for the visit:': ['It is preferable to visit it early in the morning or at sunset to enjoy calm and beautiful scenery.', 'Wear comfortable clothes, there are some high tracks to reach it.', 'Respect the sanctity of the place, as it is intended to honor the martyrs, and avoid high noise.', 'The camera is necessary to capture the wonderful looks from the top.']}
short_description: The monument of the martyrs in Baku commemorates the heroes and overlooks the scenic views of the city and the sea.
